y]] ([[Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly elected in 2011|MLAs]]) ===\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background: #efefef; border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n!Term\n!style=\"width: 90px\"|Executive\n!colspan=\"2\"|First Minister\n!colspan=\"2\"|Deputy\n!colspan=\"2\"|Parties (Ministries)\n|-  \n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[2011 Northern Ireland Assembly election|2011]]\u20132016\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Executive of the 4th Northern Ireland Assembly|3rd]]\n!rowspan=\"5\" style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"4\"| [[Peter Robinson (Northern Ireland politician)|Peter Robinson]]<ref name=\"4th Executive\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2011/0512/nielection.html|title=Robinson, McGuinness re-appointed to NI posts|last=|first=|date=12 May 2011|website=RT\u00c9|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=13 Feb 2020}}</ref>\n!rowspan=\"5\" style=\"background-color: {{Sinn F\u00e9in/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"5\"| [[Martin McGuinness]] <ref name=\"4th Executive\" />\n! style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Democratic Unionist Party|DUP]] (5 <small>until 2015</small>, 6 <small>from 2015</small>)<small>{{refn|name=UUP2015|group=nb|The UUP served in the Third Executive from 2011\u20132015, occupying one seat. The party withdrew from the Executive in October 2015, with the DUP taking over their vacant seat.}}</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Sinn F\u00e9in/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Sinn F\u00e9in|SF]] (4)\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Alliance Party of Northern Ireland/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|APNI]] (2)\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Social Democratic and Labour Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Social Democratic and Labour Party|SDLP]] (1)\n|-style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n|rowspan=\"1\"| [[Arlene Foster]]\n! style=\"background-color: {{Ulster Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Ulster Unionist Party|UUP]] (1 <small>until 2015</small>){{refn|name=UUP2015|group=nb}}\n|- style=\"text-align: left; background: #efefef; border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n|colspan=\"9\"|\n\n=== [[Executive of the 5th Northern Ireland Assembly|5th Assembly]] ([[Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly elected in 2016|MLAs]]) ===\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background: #efefef; border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n!Term\n!style=\"width: 90px\"|Executive\n!colspan=\"2\"|First Minister\n!colspan=\"2\"|Deputy\n!colspan=\"3\"|Parties (Ministries)\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[2016 Northern Ireland Assembly election|2016]]\u2013[[Renewable Heat Incentive scandal|2017]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Executive of the 5th Northern Ireland Assembly|4th]]\n!rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Arlene Foster]]\n!rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{Sinn F\u00e9in/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Martin McGuinness]]\n! style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Democratic Unionist Party|DUP]] (5)\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Sinn F\u00e9in/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Sinn F\u00e9in|SF]] (4)\n|-style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent politician/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Claire Sugden|Independent]] (1)<small>{{refn|name=Justice2016|group=nb|The Minister of Justice is not allocated through the D'Hondt mechanism because it is a contentious position. It was offered to Claire Sugden, an independent politician, who accepted the role and she was elected on a cross-community vote in the Northern Ireland Assembly. All other positions in the Executive are allocated through the D'Hondt mechanism.}}</small>\n|- style=\"text-align: left; background: #efefef; border-bottom: 2px solid gray;\"\n|colspan=\"9\"|\n\n=== [[Executive of the 6th Northern Ireland Assembly|6th Assembly]] ([[Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly elected in 2017|MLAs]]) ===\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background: #efefef; border-bottom: 2px solid gray