e|1500 m freestyle]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | 2010 Dubai | [[2010 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) \u2013 Men's 400 metre individual medley|400 m medley]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2014 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m)|2014 Doha]] | [[2014 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) \u2013 Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500 m freestyle]]}}\n{{MedalBronze | {{nowrap|2004 Indianapolis}} | 200 m medley}}\n{{MedalBronze | 2010 Dubai | [[2010 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) \u2013 Men's 200 metre freestyle|200 m freestyle]]}}\n{{MedalBronze | 2010 Dubai | [[2010 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) \u2013 Men's 400 metre freestyle|400 m freestyle]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Swimming at the Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[Swimming at the 2005 Mediterranean Games|2005 Almer\u00eda]] | 800 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2005 Almer\u00eda | 200 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2005 Almer\u00eda | 400 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | [[Swimming at the 2009 Mediterranean Games|2009 Pescara]] | 200 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2009 Pescara | 200 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2009 Pescara | 400 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2009 Pescara | 400 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2009 Pescara | 1500 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | [[Swimming at the 2013 Mediterranean Games|2013 Mersin]] | 400 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2013 Mersin | 1500 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[Swimming at the 2001 Mediterranean Games|2001 Tunis]] | 400 m medley}}\n{{MedalSilver | 2013 Mersin | 200 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalSilver | 2013 Mersin | 200 m medley}}\n{{MedalSilver | 2013 Mersin | 400 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Pan Arab Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[Swimming at the 2011 Pan Arab Games|2011 Doha]] | 50 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 100 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 200 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 400 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 1500 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 100 m backstroke}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 200 m backstroke}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | {{nowrap|200 m breaststroke}}}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 50 m butterfly}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 100 m butterfly}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 200 m butterfly}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 200 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 400 m medley}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 4\u00d7100 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalGold | 2011 Doha | 4\u00d7200 m freestyle}}\n{{MedalSilver | 2011 Doha| 4\u00d7100 m medley}}\n}}\n\n'''Oussama \"Ous\" Mellouli''' ({{lang-ar|'''\u0623\u0633\u0627\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0644\u0648\u0644\u064a'''}}; born 16 February 1984) is a Tunisian [[swimmer]] who competes in the [[freestyle swimming|freestyle]] and [[medley swimming|medley]] events. He is a three-time Olympic medalist, is an [[African records in swimming|African record]] holder, and trains with the USC Trojans team based at the [[University of Southern California]], where he studied as a computer science undergraduate and swam collegiately.\n\nSince returning from an Adderall related drugs ban, Oussama Mellouli has been the 1500 m freestyle World champion at the [[2009 World Aquatics Championships]] with a winning time of 14:37.28, then the second best performance of all time. Mellouli was the gold medalist in the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500 freestyle]] at the 2008 Olympics, the bronze medalist in the 1500 freestyle at the [[2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Olympics]], and the gold medalist in the 10&nbsp;km marathon swim at the 2012 Olympics. He is the first Olympian to win medals in both the open water and the pool in a single Olympics<ref>https://swimswam.com/ous-mellouli-looking-repeat-gold-rio/</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Tunis]], Mellouli left Tunisia at the age of 15 to study and train in [[France]]. He enrolled in [[University of Southern California|USC]] [[USC Viterbi School of Engineering|Viterbi School of Engineering]] in 2003 after graduating from the Lycee Technologique du Rempart in [[Marseille]], France. He swam for the USC Trojans and graduated in 2007 with a computer science bachelor's degree. He is a scholarship holder with the [[Olympic Solidarity]] program.{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}\n\n==Swimming Timeline==\n===2001===\nMellouli won 1 silver medal in the 400m IM at the [[2001 Mediterranean Games]], in [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]].\n\n===2003===\nMellouli first established himself on the world scene at the [[2003 World Aquatics Championships|2003 World Championships]] in [[Barcelona|Barcelona, Spain]] where he won a bronze in the 400m Individual Medley finishing behind [[L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Cseh]] and a world record performance from [[Michael Phelps]].\n\n===2004===\nAt the [[2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Olympics]] he finished 5th in the 400 IM, setting the [[African records in swimming|African Record]] in the process. He further distinguished himself at the [[2004 FINA Short Course World Championships]] in [[Indianapolis, Indiana|Indianapolis, USA]] where he won the first international-level gold medal in swimming for [[Tunisia]], in the 400m IM, finishing over a second ahead of second and third-place finishers [[Robin Francis]] and [[Eric Shanteau]]. Later on at the meet he would go on to win bronze in the 200m IM.\n\n===2005===\nHe was able to better his Athens mark with his bronze-medal swim in the 400 IM event at the [[2005 World Aquatics Championships]] in [[Montreal|Montreal, Canada]].  He also won the bronze-medal in the 400 freestyle at that same event. He also won three gold medals (800 m freestyle, 400m medley, 200m medley) at the [http://www.almeria2005.es XVth Mediterranean Games] in Almer\u00eda, Spain.\n\n===2006===\nOn 1 December 2006 Oussama Mellouli beat Michael Phelps in the 400m IM at the U.S. Open in West Lafayette: Mellouli clocked 4:15.61, ahead of Phelps with 4:18.32.<ref>[http://www.usaswimming.org/USASWeb/_Rainbow/Documents/601b51f2-d2a0-46fb-aef3-e1e9772b519b/061130F020.htm US Open 2006 results: Men's 400 IM final]. Archived on the [[USA Swimming]] website and retrieved 2009-07-23.</ref> This swim however was subsequently placed within Mellouli's 18-month doping ban, and the results nullified, as the drug test where the banned substance was found occurred at this meet (see section below for further information).\n\n===2007===\nOn 19 February 2007 he broke his own African Record in the 200m individual medley for the fourth time since 2003 at the [[USA Swimming]] Grand Prix meet, held at the [[Mizzou Aquatic Center]] at the [[University of Missouri]]. He also set a new African record in the 400 meter individual medley.\n\nOn 25 March 2007 he won the silver in the [[Swimming at the 2007 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 400 metre freestyle|400 m freestyle]] (3:45.12) at the [[2007 World Aquatics Championships|2007 World Championships]] in Melbourne, Australia. Three days later, on 28 March, he swam to the first Tunisian World Championship in swimming in winning the [[Swimming at the 2007 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 800 metre freestyle|800m freestyle]] in a then [[List of African records in swimming|African Record]] of 7:46.95 \u2014 one of the top 10 fastest times ever. However, due to his positive drug-testing result from a in-competition test from December 2006 and the 18-month competition ban imposed on him on 11 September 2007 by the [[Court of Arbitration for Sport]] (CAS), retroactive from 30 November 2006 forward, his 2007 World Championships results have been nullified. He was also a finalist in the [[Swimming at the 2007 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 400 metre individual medley|400 m individual medley]], where he originally finished fourth in 4:11.68.\n\nFollowing the 11 September 2007 ruling by CAS, Mellouli was not allowed to compete again up mid-2008. All of Mellouli's results from 2007 have been nullified, per his September 2007 doping suspension, related to his positive test from December 2006 (see section below).\n\n===2008 Olympics===\nMellouli came into the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Olympics]] in Beijing, China entered in two events, the 400m and 1500m freestyle events. In his first event, the 400m free despite setting a new African record in the final, he could only manage fifth place in a time of 3:43.45. Mellouli would however go on to win the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500m freestyle]] and set a new African record. In doing so, he became the first African male swimmer to ever win an Olympic gold medal in an individual swimming event (the South African men's 4 \u00d7 100 m Free Relay won the event at the [[Swimming at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Olympics]]).\n\n===2009===\nMellouli won 5 gold medals (200m and 400m individual medley, and 200m, 400m and 1500m freestyles) at the [[Swimming at the 2009 Mediterranean Games|XVI Mediterranean Games]] in Pescara, Italy.\n\nIn the [[2009 World Aquatics Championships]], held in Rome during the summer, Mellouli won a gold medal in the 1500 meter freestyle and 2 silver medals in the 400 meter freestyle and 800 meter freestyle.\n\n===2010===\nMellouli won 4 medals ( 1 gold in the 1500 freestyle; 1 silver in the 400 medley and 2 bronzes in the 200 m freestyle and the 400 m freestyle) at the  [[2010 FINA Short Course World Championships]] (25m) in Dubai, UAE.\n\n===2011===\nMellouli won 16 medals ( 15 gold and 1 silver ) at the [[2011 Pan Arab Games]] in Doha, Qatar.\n\n===2012===\nMellouli won 2 medals (1 gold in the [[Swimming at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's marathon 10 kilometre|10km marathon]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/london-olympics-2012/news/Mellouli-wins-mens-10km-swimming-marathon/articleshow/15436220.cms|title=Mellouli wins men's 10km swimming marathon|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref> and 1 bronze in the [[Swimming at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500m freestyle]]) at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] held in London, UK. He became the first person to win medals in both pool and open-water swimming in the same Olympics.\n\n===2013===\nMellouli won 1 gold medal in the [[Open water swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 5 km|5km marathon]] at the [[2013 World Aquatics Championships|2013 World Championships]], in [[Barcelona|Barcelona, Spain]].\n\n===2016===\nMellouli participated in two competitions in [[Rio 2016 Summer Olympics]] but did not win any medals. In the [[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics - Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500m freestyle]] he came first in his heat with 15:07.78 (considerably slower than his [[London 2012 Summer Olympics]] time of 14:40.31<ref>[https://www.olympic.org/oussama-mellouli Oussama MELLOULI - Olympic Swimming | Tunisia], olympic.org. Accessed August 23, 2016.</ref>) but ranked 21st in the competition thus did not qualify for the final. He also competed in the [[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics - Men's marathon 10 kilometre|10km marathon]] finishing in the 12th place with 1:53:06 (+0:00:07 of the gold winner).<ref>https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/oussama-mellouli</ref>.\n\n==Positive drug test==\nA few weeks after the conclusion of the [[2007 World Aquatics Championships|2007 World Championships]], reports began to surface that Mellouli had tested positive for a banned substance at the 2006 U.S. Open, 30 November \u2013 2 December 2006. These reports surfaced because [[FINA]], the international governing body of the sport, had discovered that Tunisian authorities had known about the positive test but had only given him a warning. FINA/WADA rules state that when an athlete tests positive for a banned substance, he or she must be given a 2-year ban from the sport.  Accordingly, FINA took the case to the [[Court of Arbitration for Sport]] (CAS), demanding stiffer sanction.\n\nMellouli has since admitted that he took the [[Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder|ADD]] medication [[Adderall]], a [[stimulant]] and a form of [[amphetamine]]. (Already in June 2006, an American sports commentator wrote: ''Various studies show rampant use of Adderall, Ritalin and other drugs normally used for attention deficit disorder instead applied toward all-night cramming sessions.''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060615032317/http://msnbc.msn.com/id/13214435/ \"Consider ending drug policies in sports: Maybe best solution is just to let pro athletes take whatever they want\"], Commentary by Bob Cook, ''[[MSNBC.com]]'', 10 June 2006. Retrieved on 2007-09-13.</ref> ) Mellouli did not have a prescription for the drug, having claimed to have received it from another [[University of Southern California|USC]] student shortly before the US Open. He argued that he took the pill in order to help himself with writing a [[term paper]] (to sustain or enhance his academic performance) in the days leading up to the weekend US Open meet, and that the drug was not intended as a performance-enhancing substance for competitive swimming. However, amphetamines are on the official banned substances list; and can/do help swimming performance.<ref>List of Drugs Prohibited by the WADA for years [http://www.wada-ama.org/rtecontent/document/list_2005.pdf 2005] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926025439/http://www.wada-ama.org/rtecontent/document/list_2005.pdf |date=2007-09-26 }} and [http://www.wada-ama.org/rtecontent/document/2006_LIST.pdf 2006] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080819211130/http://www.wada-ama.org/rtecontent/document/2006_LIST.pdf |date=2008-08-19 }} ([[portable document format|PDF]]) \u2013 relevant quote: ''The following stimulants are prohibited, including both their optical (D- and L-) isomers where relevant: ...amphetamine... and other substances with similar chemical structure or similar biological effect(s).'' (p. 7) This passage verbatim matches the content of article section [[Adderall#Chemistry]].</ref>\n\n{{Wikinews|Tunisian swimmer Oussama Mellouli stripped of championship for doping}}\nCAS ruled on Mellouli's case on 11 September 2007, ruling against him and issuing him an 18-month competition suspension, retroactively beginning on 30 November 2006. As a result of this sanction, all his results from the 2006 U.S. Open through the competitions his swam in 2007, including the 2007 World Championships, were nullified. His ban from competition covered most, but not all, of the qualification window for the 2008 Olympics. As the retroactive nullification of results wiped out all of his qualifying times for the 2008 Games, he ended up with just a week or two after the ban in order to qualify (which he did).\n\n==Achievements==\n* [[2013 World Aquatics Championships|2013 World Championships]] \u2013 1 gold medal ([[Open water swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 5 km|5 km marathon]]) and 1 bronze medal ([[Open water swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's 10 km|10 k marathon]])\n* [[2012 Summer Olympics]] \u2013 gold medal ([[Swimming at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's marathon 10 kilometre|10 km marathon]]) and bronze medal ([[Swimming at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 1500 metre freestyle|1500 m freestyle]]).\n* [[2009 World Aquatics Championships|2009 World Championships]] \u2013 1 gold medal (1500 m freestyle) and 2 silver medals (400 m freestyle, 800 m freestyle)\n* [[2008 Summer Olympics]] \u2013 gold medal (1500 m freestyle)\n* [[2007 World Aquatics Championships|2007 World Championships]] \u2014 ''results nullified''.\n* [[2005 World Aquatics Championships|2005 World Championships]] \u2013 bronze medal (400m individual medley and 400m freestyle)\n* [[Swimming at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 400 metre individual medley|2004 Olympic Games]] \u2013 fifth place (400 m individual medley)\n* [[2004 FINA Short Course World Championships]] \u2013 bronze medal (200 m individual medley)\n* [[2004 FINA Short Course World Championships]] \u2013 gold medal (400 m individual medley)\n* [[2003 World Aquatics Championships|2003 World Championships]] \u2013 bronze medal (400 m individual medley)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Adderall#Performance-enhancing use]]\n* [[List of sportspeople sanctioned for doping offences]]\n* [[Tunisia at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Oussama Mellouli}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070425005120/http://www-scf.usc.edu/~oman/ITP104/OusWebsite/HomePage.htm Personal webpage of Oussama Mellouli at the University of Southern California]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{succession box|title=[[List of Swimming World Swimmers of the Year#African Swimmers of the Year|African Swimmer of the Year]]|before={{flagicon|RSA}} [[Roland Schoeman]]|after={{flagicon|RSA}} [[Cameron van der Burgh]]|years=2008,<br>2009 <small>(with {{flagicon|RSA}} Cameron van der Burgh)</small>}}\n{{succession box|title=[[List of Swimming World Swimmers of the Year#Open Water Swimmers of the Year|Open Water Swimmer of the Year]]|before={{flagicon|GER}} [[Thomas Lurz]] and {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Spyridon Gianniotis]]|after=''Incumbent''|years=2012}}\n{{succession box|title=[[List of FINA Athletes of the Year#Open water swimming|FINA Open Water Swimmer of the Year]]|before={{flagicon|GER}} [[Thomas Lurz]]|after={{flagicon|GER}} [[Thomas Lurz]]|years=2012}}\n{{s-sports|oly}}\n{{succession box\n| before = [[Heykel Megannem]]\n| title = [[List of flag bearers for Tunisia at the Olympics|Flagbearer]] for {{TUN}}\n| years = [[2016 Summer Olympics|Rio de Janeiro 2016]]\n| after = ''Incumbent''\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions 1500 m Freestyle Men}}\n{{Footer Olympic Champions 10 km Marathon Men}}\n{{Footer World LC Champions 1500m Freestyle Men}}\n{{Footer World SC Champions 1500m Freestyle Men}}\n{{Footer World SC Champions 400m Medley Men}}\n{{Footer Mediterranean Champions 1500m Freestyle Men}}\n{{Footer Mediterranean Champions 200m Medley Men}}\n{{Footer Mediterranean Champions 400m Medley Men}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mellouli, Oussama}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male freestyle swimmers]]\n[[Category:Male medley swimmers]]\n[[Category:Male long-distance swimmers]]\n[[Category:Doping cases in swimming]]\n[[Category:Olympic swimmers of Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Tunis]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Tunisian expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Tunisian male swimmers]]\n[[Category:USC Trojans men's swimmers]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists in open water swimming]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m)]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games gold medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games silver medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2001 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2005 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2009 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2013 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:African Games gold medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:African Games medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2003 All-Africa Games]]\n", "name_user": "81.234.98.130", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200e2006)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oussama_Mellouli"}
{"title_page": "Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2\n| image = Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 cover.png\n| caption = Cover art for ''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''\n| developer = [[Traveller's Tales]]\n| publisher = [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]], [[Feral Interactive]] (macOS)\n| series =\n| director = Stephen Sharples<br>Arthur Parsons\n| producer = Jennifer Burbeck<br>David Geeson\n| designer = Arthur Parsons\n| programmer = Steve Harding a Bad programmer\n| artist = Leon Warren\n| writer = [[Kurt Busiek]]<br>Stephen Sharples\n| composer = Ian Livingstone\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Nintendo Switch]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[macOS]]}}\n| released = {{Collapsible list\n| title = 14 November 2017\n| titlestyle = font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;\n| '''macOS'''{{Video game release|WW|2 August 2018}}\n}}\n| genre = [[Bad game|Bad game]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n}}\n'''''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''''' is a [[Lego]]-themed [[action-adventure game|action-adventure]] [[video game]] developed by [[Traveller's Tales]] and published by [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]] for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Nintendo Switch]] and [[Xbox One]] on 14 November 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/05/lego_marvel_super_heroes_2_confirmed_for_nintendo_switch |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Confirmed for Nintendo Switch |first=Thomas |last=Whitehead |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/5/15/15640804/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-pc-ps4-switch-xbox-one |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 coming to PC, PS4, Switch, Xbox One |first=Samit |last=Sarkar |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> and by [[Feral Interactive]] for [[macOS]] on 2 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.feralinteractive.com/en/news/891/ |title=Be transported into the Marvel Universe with LEGO\u00ae Marvel Super Heroes 2, out now for macOS! |date=2 August 2018 |accessdate=2 August 2018}}</ref> It is the sequel to 2013's ''[[Lego Marvel Super Heroes]]'' and the third installment of the ''Lego Marvel'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-officially-announced-wi/1100-6450040/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 Officially Announced With New Teaser |first=Tamoor |last=Hussain |date=26 May 2017 |website=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref>\n\nWith the core gameplay following the same style of past ''Lego'' titles are not original and this game can go right in the trash. The  game features the ability to Have all characters so you can waste $20.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vg247.com/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-superheroes-2-is-here-to-save-the-year/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 is here to save the year |first=Sherif |last=Saed |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[VG247]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> ''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''{{'}}s storyline centers around superheroes from different eras and realities of the [[Marvel Universe so they cane have a excuse to put all worlds in 1 ]] as they fight against the time-travelling villain [[Kang the Conqueror]] in a battle across space and time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-takes-to-the-future-and-the-past.aspx |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 Takes To The Future & The Past |first=Matthew |last=Kato |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Game Informer]] |publisher=[[GameStop]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2'' is an [[action-adventure]] game played from a [[Third-person view|third-person perspective]]. The game features a similar gameplay to its predecessors and other [[List of Lego video games|Lego video games]], alternating between various action-adventure sequences and puzzle-solving scenarios.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-15-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-announced |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 announced |first=Tom |last=Phillips |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> The ability to manipulate time is allowed to players directly from the new [[open world]] of [[Chronopolis (Marvel Comics)|Chronopolis]], which is a myriad of 17 different Marvel locations (consisting of a variation of [[Ancient Egypt]], an apocalyptic [[Asgard (comics)|Asgard]], [[Attilan]], Hala, the [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]] Empire, [[K'un-L'un]], [[Knowhere]], [[Features of the Marvel Universe#Regions and countries|Lemuria]], [[Man-Thing]]'s Swamp, [[Manhattan]], an [[Avataars: Covenant of the Shield|alternate version of Medieval England]], a [[Marvel Noir]] version of [[New York City]] called Manhattan Noir, [[Marvel 2099|Nueva York]], a variation of the [[American frontier|Old West]], Sakaar, [[Wakanda]], and [[Xandar]]) linked through time and space and surrounding Kang the Conqueror's Citadel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-is-flying-to-switch-ps4-xbox-one-and-pc/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 is flying to Switch, PS4, Xbox One, and PC |first=Mike |last=Minotti |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[VentureBeat]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> The game also introduces a new four-player competitive Super Hero battle mode, allowing players to fight each other cooperatively in battle arenas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-release-date |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 coming November 17, watch a teaser trailer with Baby Groot |first=Richard |last=Scott-Jones |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[PCGamesN]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-releases-november-14-ps4-xbox-one-pc/ |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Coming to PS4, Xbox & PC |first=Jason |last=Dunning |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[PlayStation LifeStyle]] |publisher=[[CraveOnline]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Characters===\nMuch like the two previous Lego Marvel games, the players are able to take control of a roster of iconic characters from the [[Marvel Universe]], each with their own unique abilities. For example, [[Star-Lord]] is capable of flight, [[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]] can activate claw switches, and [[Spider-Man]] can swing on his webs, crawl on walls and use his spider-sense to detect hidden objects. The game also features characters from different time periods and realities over the Marvel Universe, which includes [[Spider-Woman (Gwen Stacy)|Spider-Gwen]], a cowboy version of [[Captain America]], a [[Alternative versions of the Hulk#Avataars: Covenant of the Shield|medieval counterpart of]] [[Hulk]], and many others.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-gets-teased-full-trailer-to-be-shown-may-23-436216.phtml |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 gets teased, full trailer to be shown May 23 |first=Peter |last=Glagowski |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Destructoid]] |publisher=Enthusiast Gaming |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> In addition, the game also features variations of sundry characters, like Iron Duck (who is merely [[Howard the Duck]] wearing the [[Iron Man's armor]]) and Carnom (a fusion of the [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]] symbiote and the [[Carnage (comics)|Carnage]] symbiote that is exclusive to the game).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2017/07/sdcc-howard-the-duck-iron-duck-and-carnom-come-to-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2/ |title=Howard the Duck and Carnom come to Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 |first=Gary |last=Collinson |date=21 July 2017 |website=Flickering Myth |accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile some characters are just based on the comic books, others have their visuals taken from the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], such as the [[Guardians of the Galaxy (2008 team)|Guardians of the Galaxy]], [[Doctor Strange]], and [[Scott Lang (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Ant-Man]]. Using the ability to manipulate time, the players can change the look and abilities of certain characters. For instance, they can take Baby Groot (from the ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'') and move time forward for him to become his [[Groot|adult version]], and Spider-Man can go both ways with his [[Spider-Man Noir|Noir]] and [[Spider-Man 2099|2099]] counterparts.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2017/05/16/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-announced/ |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 KONK!ing to November |first=Alice |last=O'Connor |date=16 May 2017 |website=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Downloadable content===\nOn 6 October, ten [[Downloadable content|DLC]] packs were announced for the game. Of these ten, there are six level packs and four character packs based on Marvel Cinematic Universe films, superhero teams, and time variant heroes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/09/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-season-pass-content-mcu-packs-revealed |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Season Pass Content, MCU Packs Revealed |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=9 October 2017 |website=IGN |language=en-US |access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n*On 19 December, two character packs were released. [[Agents of Atlas]] features the playable characters [[Jimmy Woo]], [[Gorilla-Man]], [[The Uranian]], [[M-11 (comics)|M-11]] and [[Venus (Marvel Comics)|Venus]]. The [[Guardians of the Galaxy|Classic Guardians]] pack features [[Charlie-27]], [[Major Astro]], [[Martinex]], [[Yondu]], [[Starhawk (comics)|Starhawk]], [[Aleta Ogord]] and [[Nikki (comics)|Nikki]].\n* On 19 December, a ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'' level pack was released, featuring a level based on the opening scene of the film. It adds several new characters, including [[Kraglin]], [[Starhawk (comics)|Stakar Ogord]], Tullk Ul-Zyn, [[Ego the Living Planet|Ego]] and variants of [[Star-Lord]] and [[Rocket Raccoon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comingsoon.net/games/news/910433-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-dlc-adds-guardians-vol-2-characters#/slide/1 |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 DLC adds Guardians Vol. 2 characters |first=Spencer |last=Perry |date=19 December 2017 |website=[[ComingSoon.net]] |accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>\n* On 18 January, a [[The Champions (comics)|Champions]] character pack was released featuring [[Moon Girl (Marvel Comics)|Moon Girl]], [[Devil Dinosaur]], [[Viv Vision]], [[Amadeus Cho]] and the [[Nova (Sam Alexander)|Sam Alexander]] and [[Nadia Pym]] incarnations of [[Nova (comics)|Nova]] and [[Wasp (Marvel Comics)|Wasp]] as well as [[Hawkeye (Kate Bishop)|Kate Bishop]] as [[Hawkeye (Kate Bishop)|Hawkeye]]\n* On 13 February, a ''[[Black Panther (2018 film)|Black Panther]]'' level pack was released. It features new characters from the film, such as [[Okoye (comics)|Okoye]], [[Malice (comics)|Nakia]], [[Everett K. Ross|Everett Ross]], [[Klaw (Marvel Comics)|Ulysses Klaue]] and [[Erik Killmonger]]. However, the level included had no connection to the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/02/13/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-black-panther-dlc-revealed |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Black Panther DLC Revealed |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=13 February 2018 |website=IGN |language=en-US |access-date=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n* On 20 March, a ''[[Cloak and Dagger (comics)|Cloak and Dagger]]'' level pack was released, and introduced the playable characters [[Cloak and Dagger (comics)|Cloak and Dagger]], [[Mister Negative]], [[Blackout (Marcus Daniels)|Blackout]], [[Shroud (comics)|Shroud]], [[Nightmare (Marvel Comics)|Nightmare]], and [[Silvermane]]. The level included takes place immediately after Cloak and Dagger gain their powers, and involves them escaping their evil captor.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbr.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-cloak-and-dagger-dlc/ |title=Cloak & Dagger Join LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 |date=20 March 2018 |work=CBR |access-date=21 April 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n* On 10 April, a ''[[Runaways (comics)|Runaways]]'' level pack was released, which includes characters such as [[Nico Minoru]], [[Chase Stein]], [[Alex Wilder]], [[Karolina Dean]], [[Molly Hayes]], [[Gertrude Yorkes]], and [[Old Lace (comics)|Old Lace]]. The level is based on a story from the comic series, wherein the team travels to Marine Vivarium and encounters the [[Pride (comics)|Pride]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/games/2401731/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-adds-the-runaways-via-dlc |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Adds The Runaways Via DLC |date=12 April 2018 |work=CINEMABLEND |access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n* On 24 April, a level pack inspired by ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' was released, which includes an original level where the player controls the [[Black Order (comics)|Black Order]] as they invade [[Attilan]]. The pack unlocks [[Hulkbuster armor|Hulkbuster 2.0]] and an adolescent [[Groot]], as well as [[Thanos]] and the Black Order (consisting of [[Corvus Glaive]], [[Black Dwarf (comics)|Cull Obsidian]], [[Proxima Midnight]], and [[Ebony Maw]]).<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.comingsoon.net/games/news/939179-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-gets-infinity-war-dlc |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Gets Infinity War DLC |date=19 April 2018 |work=ComingSoon.net |access-date=21 April 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n* On 6 July, a final level pack inspired by ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp]]'' was released, which includes an original level featuring [[Scott Lang|Ant-Man]] and the [[Hope Pym|Wasp]] as they try to recover [[Hank Pym]]'s original Ant-Man helmet from [[Egghead (Marvel Comics)|Egghead]], who plans to use it to create some [[Artificial intelligence|AI]] Avengers. The DLC adds 8 new characters to the game: the \"Ant-Man and the Wasp\" version of Ant-Man (Scott Lang), the MCU version of the Wasp (Hope van Dyne), [[Crossfire (comics)|Crossfire]], Egghead, the MCU version of [[Ghost (Marvel comics)|Ghost]], [[Giant-Man]] (Raz Malhotra), [[Human Fly (comics)|The Human Fly]] and [[Cassandra Lang|Stinger (Cassie Lang)]].\n\n==Plot==\nThe [[Guardians of the Galaxy (2008 team)|Guardians of the Galaxy]] help defend [[Xandar]] from an attack by [[Kang the Conqueror]], who wields a time crystal. Kang's ship, the ''Damocles'', launches devices which cause a section of Xandar to disappear. Meanwhile, at [[Avengers Mansion]], [[Nick Fury (Ultimate Marvel character)|Nick Fury]] presents the [[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]] with several missions: [[Captain America]], [[She-Hulk]], and [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|Thor]] fight the [[Presence (Marvel Comics)|Presence]] in [[Siberia]]; [[Iron Man]] and [[Carol Danvers|Captain Marvel]] defeat [[Attuma]] at his underwater base; and [[Spider-Man]], [[Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)|Ms. Marvel]], and [[White Tiger (Ava Ayala)|White Tiger]] battle several escaped supervillains on the [[Brooklyn Bridge]]. The Guardians arrive just before Kang, who uses his devices to steal [[Manhattan]] with the heroes inside it and makes it part of his battle arena called [[Chronopolis (Marvel Comics)|Chronopolis]], consisting of various locales that he has stolen from across time and space with his citadel at its center.\n\nCaptain America leads a team through a portal to Medieval England, where they help [[Black Knight (Sir Percy)|Sir Percy]] reclaim his castle from the [[Enchantress (Marvel Comics)|Enchantress]] and [[Black Knight (Nathan Garrett)|Nathan Garrett]]. A team led by She-Hulk follows [[Klaw (Marvel Comics)|Klaw]] through a portal to [[Wakanda]], where [[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]] joins them to fight [[Man-Ape]] in the [[vibranium]] mines. The heroes converge in a version of Manhattan ruled by [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]], where they battle Klaw and vibranium soldiers created by [[Arnim Zola]], and defeat [[Helmut Zemo|Baron Zemo]] in a [[dogfight]]. Thor, Captain Marvel, and She-Hulk travel to a swamp where they vanquish [[Man-Thing]]. Kang reveals that Man-Thing was guarding the Nexus of All Realities, which kept the various realms of Chronopolis separated. Kang destroys the Nexus and challenges the heroes to rise up and face him.\n\nRegrouping at Avengers Mansion, the heroes detect a faint signal from outside Chronopolis. Searching for a device to boost its strength, the Guardians travel to the [[American frontier|Old West]] where they battle [[MODOK]] and the [[Circus of Crime]]. Retrieving the device, they learn that the signal is being sent from [[Knowhere]] by [[Cosmo the Spacedog]]. The heroes plan to retrieve the fragments of the Nexus in order to bring Knowhere into Chronopolis and use its energies to bring down the barrier surrounding Kang's citadel. In preparation, [[Doctor Strange]] leads a team to the [[Sanctum Sanctorum]] where they fight [[Baron Mordo]] and retrieve the Book of the Vishanti, while Thor leads a party to apocalyptic [[Asgard (comics)|Asgard]] to enlist the aid of [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]], facing [[Surtur (Marvel Comics)|Surtur]] in the process.\n\nThe search for the five Nexus fragments again splits the heroes into teams. Captain America's group travels to the underwater city of Lemuria, but falls into a trap and must battle the Red King and several versions of the [[Hulk]] in Sakaar. Joined by the Hulk and [[Stingray (comics)|Stingray]], they return to Lemuria and defeat Attuma, retrieving a fragment. Moving on to [[Ancient Egypt]], they enter a [[Sphinx]] and join Horus of the [[Heliopolitans]] in facing [[Loki (comics)|Loki]] and [[N'Kantu, the Living Mummy]] to obtain another. Spider-Man's group visits the ''[[Marvel Noir]]'' version of Manhattan, where they help [[Iron Fist (comics)|Iron Fist]], [[Daredevil (Marvel Comics character)|Daredevil]], [[Luke Cage]], and [[Spider-Man Noir]] defeat the [[Kingpin (character)|Kingpin]]. Iron Fist accompanies them to K'un-L'un, where they fight [[Steel Serpent]] to free [[Shou-Lao]] and retrieve a Nexus fragment. Proceeding to the [[Alchemax]] building in ''[[Marvel 2099]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Nueva York, [[Spider-Gwen]] and [[Spider-Man 2099]] help them defeat the ''2099'' version of [[Green Goblin]] and a fusion of [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]] and [[Carnage (comics)|Carnage]] to obtain another fragment. In the [[Kree]] home world of Hala, the Guardians battle [[Ronan the Accuser]]. Meanwhile, in Attilan, the [[Inhumans]] defeat [[Maximus (comics)|Maximus]]. [[Black Bolt]] and [[Medusa (comics)|Medusa]] then head to Hala, where they free the Guardians from the control of the [[Supreme Intelligence]] and help them retrieve another fragment. As Kang observes the heroes' exploits and plots to destroy them, his assistant [[Ravonna]] becomes increasingly disturbed by his actions.\n\nWith the fragments gathered, the heroes assemble a device to bring Knowhere through a portal opened by Doctor Strange. Their first attempt nearly brings [[Ego the Living Planet]] through instead. Once Knowhere is in Chronopolis, they use an [[electromagnetic pulse]] to knock out the energy shield protecting Kang's citadel. As they begin their assault, Kang summons the ''Damocles''. Iron Man, Spider-Man, and [[Star-Lord]] disable the ship, battling [[Korvac]] and escaping before it crashes. Captain America, Captain Marvel, Doctor Strange, and Star-Lord enter the citadel and face Kang, who grows to gigantic size, uses the time crystal to reverse the ''Damocles''<nowiki>'</nowiki> destruction, and wields it as a sword. Captain America creates a giant solid hologram of himself and uses it to defeat Kang. Ravonna betrays Kang and uses the time crystal to turn him into a baby. The heroes celebrate their victory, and Ravonna promises to return the components of Chronopolis to their original places in time and space once the remaining villains are dealt with.\n\nIn a [[post-credits scene]], with everything restored to normal, Iron Man, Captain America, and Captain Marvel are visited by Ravonna in her new alias as Terminatrix. She is accompanied by an elderly Kang, the Supreme Intelligence, Cosmo, and Man-Thing, who inform the Avengers of a \"chronal fracture incident\".\n\n==Audio==\nDue to the game being affected by the [[2016\u201317 video game voice actor strike]], the cast from the previous game as well from ''[[Lego Marvel's Avengers]]'' did not return to reprise their roles as they were affiliated with the [[SAG-AFTRA|Screen Actors Guild\u2010American Federation of Television and Radio Artists (SAG-AFTRA)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nintendoeverything.com/lego-marvel-2-spotted-on-voice-actor-strike-document/ |title=\"LEGO Marvel 2\" spotted on voice actor strike document |author=Brian |date=3 November 2016 |website=Nintendo Everything}}</ref> While in favor of a new voice cast, [[Greg Miller (Internet celebrity)|Greg Miller]] voices [[Howard the Duck]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/agentm/status/888135929151447040 |title=#LEGOMarvel2 reveal: @GameOverGreggy voicing Howard the Duck who becomes the Iron Duck. Big role for Howard in the game. #MarvelGamesSDCC |first=Ryan |last=Penagos |date=20 July 2017 |website=twitter.com}}</ref> [[Peter Serafinowicz]] voices the game's antagonist Kang the Conqueror,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/arthur_parsons/status/905827593206865920 |title=Correct! |first=arthur |last=parsons |date=7 September 2017 |website=twitter.com}}</ref> [[Sacha Dhawan]] reprised his role as [[Steel Serpent]] from the ''[[Iron Fist (TV series)|Iron Fist]]'' [[Netflix]] television series<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/07/24/steel-serpent-explained-who-is-the-iron-fist-season-2-villain |title=Steel Serpent Explained: Who Is Davos, the Netflix Iron Fist Season 2 Villain? |first=Jesse |last=Schedeen |date=24 July 2018 |website=ign.com}}</ref> and Marvel Comics writer [[Stan Lee]] returned to voice himself.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/video-games/Lego-Marvel-Superheroes-2/Stan-Lee/ |title=Stan Lee |author= |date= |website=Behind The Voice Actors}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (XONE) 76/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref><br>(NS) 75/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for Switch Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref><br>(PS4) 73/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for PlayStation 4 Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>\n}}\nThe game was well received by critics, who praised the game's linguistic content as well as the possibility to play with various Marvel characters.\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Result !! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Game Critics Awards]]\n| Best Family/Social Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/nominees.html |title=Game Critics Awards: Best of E3 2017 (2017 Nominees) |website=[[Game Critics Awards]] |accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Gamescom|Gamescom 2017]]\n| Best Family Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cgmagonline.com/2017/08/21/gamescom-2017-award-nominees/ |title=Gamescom 2017 Award Nominees |first=Zubi |last=Khan |date=21 August 2017 |website=CGM |accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\" | New York Game Awards 2018\n| Central Park Children's Zoo Award for Best Kids Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.axs.com/complete-list-of-winners-of-the-new-york-game-awards-2018-127527 |title=Complete list of winners of the New York Game Awards 2018 |first=Kayla |last=Whitney |date=25 January 2018 |website=[[AXS (company)|AXS]] |accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] Awards\n| Performance in a Comedy, Supporting <small>(Dar Dash)</small>\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/ |title=Nominee List for 2017 |date=9 February 2018 |website=[[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] |accessdate=19 February 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180215172210/http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/ |archive-date=15 February 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/ |title=Horizon wins 7; Mario GOTY |date=13 March 2018 |website=[[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] |accessdate=15 March 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180314070824/http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/ |archive-date=14 March 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Nickelodeon]]'s [[2018 Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Video Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nickpress.com/press-releases/2018/02/26/nickelodeon-announces-2018-kids-choice-awards-nominations |title=NICKELODEON ANNOUNCES 2018 KIDS\u2019 CHOICE AWARDS NOMINATIONS |website=[[Nick.com]] |publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]] |date=26 February 2018 |accessdate=3 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.etonline.com/2018-kids-choice-awards-the-complete-winners-list-99000 |title=2018 Kids' Choice Awards: The Complete Winners List |first=Jennifer |last=Drysdale |date=24 March 2018 |website=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Develop (magazine)|Develop Awards]]\n| Animation\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mcvuk.com/development/announcing-the-develop-awards-2018-nominations-shortlist |title=Announcing the Develop Awards 2018 nominations shortlist |author=MCV staff |date=21 May 2018 |website=[[MCV (magazine)|MCV]] |accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{imdb title|7175178}}\n\n{{Lego video games}}\n{{Marvel Video Game Crossovers}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Action-adventure games]]\n[[Category:Crossover video games]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Stan Lee]]\n[[Category:Lego video games|Marvel Super Heroes 2]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Open world video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Sentient toys in fiction]]\n[[Category:Superhero video games]]\n[[Category:Traveller's Tales games]]\n[[Category:Video game sequels]]\n[[Category:Video games based on Marvel Comics]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 1933]] <!--Noir world-->\n[[Category:Video games set in the 2090s]] <!--2099 world-->\n[[Category:Video games set in Africa]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Egypt]]\n[[Category:Video games set in England]]\n[[Category:Video games set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One X enhanced games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2\n| image = Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 cover.png\n| caption = Cover art for ''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''\n| developer = [[Traveller's Tales]]\n| publisher = [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]], [[Feral Interactive]] (macOS)\n| series =\n| director = Stephen Sharples<br>Arthur Parsons\n| producer = Jennifer Burbeck<br>David Geeson\n| designer = Arthur Parsons\n| programmer = Steve Harding\n| artist = Leon Warren\n| writer = [[Kurt Busiek]]<br>Stephen Sharples\n| composer = Ian Livingstone\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Nintendo Switch]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[macOS]]}}\n| released = {{Collapsible list\n| title = 14 November 2017\n| titlestyle = font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;\n| '''macOS'''{{Video game release|WW|2 August 2018}}\n}}\n| genre = [[Bad game|Action-adventure]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n}}\n'''''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''''' is a [[Lego]]-themed [[action-adventure game|action-adventure]] [[video game]] developed by [[Traveller's Tales]] and published by [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]] for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Nintendo Switch]] and [[Xbox One]] on 14 November 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/05/lego_marvel_super_heroes_2_confirmed_for_nintendo_switch |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Confirmed for Nintendo Switch |first=Thomas |last=Whitehead |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/5/15/15640804/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-pc-ps4-switch-xbox-one |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 coming to PC, PS4, Switch, Xbox One |first=Samit |last=Sarkar |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> and by [[Feral Interactive]] for [[macOS]] on 2 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.feralinteractive.com/en/news/891/ |title=Be transported into the Marvel Universe with LEGO\u00ae Marvel Super Heroes 2, out now for macOS! |date=2 August 2018 |accessdate=2 August 2018}}</ref> It is the sequel to 2013's ''[[Lego Marvel Super Heroes]]'' and the third installment of the ''Lego Marvel'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-officially-announced-wi/1100-6450040/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 Officially Announced With New Teaser |first=Tamoor |last=Hussain |date=26 May 2017 |website=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref>\n\nWith the core gameplay following the same style of past ''Lego'' titles, the game features the ability to manipulate time and a four-player competitive Super Hero battle mode.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vg247.com/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-superheroes-2-is-here-to-save-the-year/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 is here to save the year |first=Sherif |last=Saed |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[VG247]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> ''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2''{{'}}s storyline centers around superheroes from different eras and realities of the [[Marvel Universe]] as they fight against the time-travelling villain [[Kang the Conqueror]] in a battle across space and time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-takes-to-the-future-and-the-past.aspx |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 Takes To The Future & The Past |first=Matthew |last=Kato |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Game Informer]] |publisher=[[GameStop]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2'' is an [[action-adventure]] game played from a [[Third-person view|third-person perspective]]. The game features a similar gameplay to its predecessors and other [[List of Lego video games|Lego video games]], alternating between various action-adventure sequences and puzzle-solving scenarios.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-15-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-announced |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 announced |first=Tom |last=Phillips |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> The ability to manipulate time is allowed to players directly from the new [[open world]] of [[Chronopolis (Marvel Comics)|Chronopolis]], which is a myriad of 17 different Marvel locations (consisting of a variation of [[Ancient Egypt]], an apocalyptic [[Asgard (comics)|Asgard]], [[Attilan]], Hala, the [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]] Empire, [[K'un-L'un]], [[Knowhere]], [[Features of the Marvel Universe#Regions and countries|Lemuria]], [[Man-Thing]]'s Swamp, [[Manhattan]], an [[Avataars: Covenant of the Shield|alternate version of Medieval England]], a [[Marvel Noir]] version of [[New York City]] called Manhattan Noir, [[Marvel 2099|Nueva York]], a variation of the [[American frontier|Old West]], Sakaar, [[Wakanda]], and [[Xandar]]) linked through time and space and surrounding Kang the Conqueror's Citadel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-is-flying-to-switch-ps4-xbox-one-and-pc/ |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 is flying to Switch, PS4, Xbox One, and PC |first=Mike |last=Minotti |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[VentureBeat]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> The game also introduces a new four-player competitive Super Hero battle mode, allowing players to fight each other cooperatively in battle arenas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-release-date |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 coming November 17, watch a teaser trailer with Baby Groot |first=Richard |last=Scott-Jones |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[PCGamesN]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2017/05/15/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-releases-november-14-ps4-xbox-one-pc/ |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Coming to PS4, Xbox & PC |first=Jason |last=Dunning |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[PlayStation LifeStyle]] |publisher=[[CraveOnline]] |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Characters===\nMuch like the two previous Lego Marvel games, the players are able to take control of a roster of iconic characters from the [[Marvel Universe]], each with their own unique abilities. For example, [[Star-Lord]] is capable of flight, [[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]] can activate claw switches, and [[Spider-Man]] can swing on his webs, crawl on walls and use his spider-sense to detect hidden objects. The game also features characters from different time periods and realities over the Marvel Universe, which includes [[Spider-Woman (Gwen Stacy)|Spider-Gwen]], a cowboy version of [[Captain America]], a [[Alternative versions of the Hulk#Avataars: Covenant of the Shield|medieval counterpart of]] [[Hulk]], and many others.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-gets-teased-full-trailer-to-be-shown-may-23-436216.phtml |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 gets teased, full trailer to be shown May 23 |first=Peter |last=Glagowski |date=15 May 2017 |website=[[Destructoid]] |publisher=Enthusiast Gaming |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> In addition, the game also features variations of sundry characters, like Iron Duck (who is merely [[Howard the Duck]] wearing the [[Iron Man's armor]]) and Carnom (a fusion of the [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]] symbiote and the [[Carnage (comics)|Carnage]] symbiote that is exclusive to the game).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2017/07/sdcc-howard-the-duck-iron-duck-and-carnom-come-to-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2/ |title=Howard the Duck and Carnom come to Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 |first=Gary |last=Collinson |date=21 July 2017 |website=Flickering Myth |accessdate=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhile some characters are just based on the comic books, others have their visuals taken from the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], such as the [[Guardians of the Galaxy (2008 team)|Guardians of the Galaxy]], [[Doctor Strange]], and [[Scott Lang (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Ant-Man]]. Using the ability to manipulate time, the players can change the look and abilities of certain characters. For instance, they can take Baby Groot (from the ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'') and move time forward for him to become his [[Groot|adult version]], and Spider-Man can go both ways with his [[Spider-Man Noir|Noir]] and [[Spider-Man 2099|2099]] counterparts.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2017/05/16/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-announced/ |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 KONK!ing to November |first=Alice |last=O'Connor |date=16 May 2017 |website=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Downloadable content===\nOn 6 October, ten [[Downloadable content|DLC]] packs were announced for the game. Of these ten, there are six level packs and four character packs based on Marvel Cinematic Universe films, superhero teams, and time variant heroes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/09/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-season-pass-content-mcu-packs-revealed |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Season Pass Content, MCU Packs Revealed |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=9 October 2017 |website=IGN |language=en-US |access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n*On 19 December, two character packs were released. [[Agents of Atlas]] features the playable characters [[Jimmy Woo]], [[Gorilla-Man]], [[The Uranian]], [[M-11 (comics)|M-11]] and [[Venus (Marvel Comics)|Venus]]. The [[Guardians of the Galaxy|Classic Guardians]] pack features [[Charlie-27]], [[Major Astro]], [[Martinex]], [[Yondu]], [[Starhawk (comics)|Starhawk]], [[Aleta Ogord]] and [[Nikki (comics)|Nikki]].\n* On 19 December, a ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'' level pack was released, featuring a level based on the opening scene of the film. It adds several new characters, including [[Kraglin]], [[Starhawk (comics)|Stakar Ogord]], Tullk Ul-Zyn, [[Ego the Living Planet|Ego]] and variants of [[Star-Lord]] and [[Rocket Raccoon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comingsoon.net/games/news/910433-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-dlc-adds-guardians-vol-2-characters#/slide/1 |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 DLC adds Guardians Vol. 2 characters |first=Spencer |last=Perry |date=19 December 2017 |website=[[ComingSoon.net]] |accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>\n* On 18 January, a [[The Champions (comics)|Champions]] character pack was released featuring [[Moon Girl (Marvel Comics)|Moon Girl]], [[Devil Dinosaur]], [[Viv Vision]], [[Amadeus Cho]] and the [[Nova (Sam Alexander)|Sam Alexander]] and [[Nadia Pym]] incarnations of [[Nova (comics)|Nova]] and [[Wasp (Marvel Comics)|Wasp]] as well as [[Hawkeye (Kate Bishop)|Kate Bishop]] as [[Hawkeye (Kate Bishop)|Hawkeye]]\n* On 13 February, a ''[[Black Panther (2018 film)|Black Panther]]'' level pack was released. It features new characters from the film, such as [[Okoye (comics)|Okoye]], [[Malice (comics)|Nakia]], [[Everett K. Ross|Everett Ross]], [[Klaw (Marvel Comics)|Ulysses Klaue]] and [[Erik Killmonger]]. However, the level included had no connection to the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/02/13/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-black-panther-dlc-revealed |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Black Panther DLC Revealed |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=13 February 2018 |website=IGN |language=en-US |access-date=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n* On 20 March, a ''[[Cloak and Dagger (comics)|Cloak and Dagger]]'' level pack was released, and introduced the playable characters [[Cloak and Dagger (comics)|Cloak and Dagger]], [[Mister Negative]], [[Blackout (Marcus Daniels)|Blackout]], [[Shroud (comics)|Shroud]], [[Nightmare (Marvel Comics)|Nightmare]], and [[Silvermane]]. The level included takes place immediately after Cloak and Dagger gain their powers, and involves them escaping their evil captor.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbr.com/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-cloak-and-dagger-dlc/ |title=Cloak & Dagger Join LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 |date=20 March 2018 |work=CBR |access-date=21 April 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n* On 10 April, a ''[[Runaways (comics)|Runaways]]'' level pack was released, which includes characters such as [[Nico Minoru]], [[Chase Stein]], [[Alex Wilder]], [[Karolina Dean]], [[Molly Hayes]], [[Gertrude Yorkes]], and [[Old Lace (comics)|Old Lace]]. The level is based on a story from the comic series, wherein the team travels to Marine Vivarium and encounters the [[Pride (comics)|Pride]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/games/2401731/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-adds-the-runaways-via-dlc |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Adds The Runaways Via DLC |date=12 April 2018 |work=CINEMABLEND |access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n* On 24 April, a level pack inspired by ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' was released, which includes an original level where the player controls the [[Black Order (comics)|Black Order]] as they invade [[Attilan]]. The pack unlocks [[Hulkbuster armor|Hulkbuster 2.0]] and an adolescent [[Groot]], as well as [[Thanos]] and the Black Order (consisting of [[Corvus Glaive]], [[Black Dwarf (comics)|Cull Obsidian]], [[Proxima Midnight]], and [[Ebony Maw]]).<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.comingsoon.net/games/news/939179-lego-marvel-super-heroes-2-gets-infinity-war-dlc |title=LEGO Marvel Super Heroes 2 Gets Infinity War DLC |date=19 April 2018 |work=ComingSoon.net |access-date=21 April 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n* On 6 July, a final level pack inspired by ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp]]'' was released, which includes an original level featuring [[Scott Lang|Ant-Man]] and the [[Hope Pym|Wasp]] as they try to recover [[Hank Pym]]'s original Ant-Man helmet from [[Egghead (Marvel Comics)|Egghead]], who plans to use it to create some [[Artificial intelligence|AI]] Avengers. The DLC adds 8 new characters to the game: the \"Ant-Man and the Wasp\" version of Ant-Man (Scott Lang), the MCU version of the Wasp (Hope van Dyne), [[Crossfire (comics)|Crossfire]], Egghead, the MCU version of [[Ghost (Marvel comics)|Ghost]], [[Giant-Man]] (Raz Malhotra), [[Human Fly (comics)|The Human Fly]] and [[Cassandra Lang|Stinger (Cassie Lang)]].\n\n==Plot==\nThe [[Guardians of the Galaxy (2008 team)|Guardians of the Galaxy]] help defend [[Xandar]] from an attack by [[Kang the Conqueror]], who wields a time crystal. Kang's ship, the ''Damocles'', launches devices which cause a section of Xandar to disappear. Meanwhile, at [[Avengers Mansion]], [[Nick Fury (Ultimate Marvel character)|Nick Fury]] presents the [[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]] with several missions: [[Captain America]], [[She-Hulk]], and [[Thor (Marvel Comics)|Thor]] fight the [[Presence (Marvel Comics)|Presence]] in [[Siberia]]; [[Iron Man]] and [[Carol Danvers|Captain Marvel]] defeat [[Attuma]] at his underwater base; and [[Spider-Man]], [[Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)|Ms. Marvel]], and [[White Tiger (Ava Ayala)|White Tiger]] battle several escaped supervillains on the [[Brooklyn Bridge]]. The Guardians arrive just before Kang, who uses his devices to steal [[Manhattan]] with the heroes inside it and makes it part of his battle arena called [[Chronopolis (Marvel Comics)|Chronopolis]], consisting of various locales that he has stolen from across time and space with his citadel at its center.\n\nCaptain America leads a team through a portal to Medieval England, where they help [[Black Knight (Sir Percy)|Sir Percy]] reclaim his castle from the [[Enchantress (Marvel Comics)|Enchantress]] and [[Black Knight (Nathan Garrett)|Nathan Garrett]]. A team led by She-Hulk follows [[Klaw (Marvel Comics)|Klaw]] through a portal to [[Wakanda]], where [[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]] joins them to fight [[Man-Ape]] in the [[vibranium]] mines. The heroes converge in a version of Manhattan ruled by [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]], where they battle Klaw and vibranium soldiers created by [[Arnim Zola]], and defeat [[Helmut Zemo|Baron Zemo]] in a [[dogfight]]. Thor, Captain Marvel, and She-Hulk travel to a swamp where they vanquish [[Man-Thing]]. Kang reveals that Man-Thing was guarding the Nexus of All Realities, which kept the various realms of Chronopolis separated. Kang destroys the Nexus and challenges the heroes to rise up and face him.\n\nRegrouping at Avengers Mansion, the heroes detect a faint signal from outside Chronopolis. Searching for a device to boost its strength, the Guardians travel to the [[American frontier|Old West]] where they battle [[MODOK]] and the [[Circus of Crime]]. Retrieving the device, they learn that the signal is being sent from [[Knowhere]] by [[Cosmo the Spacedog]]. The heroes plan to retrieve the fragments of the Nexus in order to bring Knowhere into Chronopolis and use its energies to bring down the barrier surrounding Kang's citadel. In preparation, [[Doctor Strange]] leads a team to the [[Sanctum Sanctorum]] where they fight [[Baron Mordo]] and retrieve the Book of the Vishanti, while Thor leads a party to apocalyptic [[Asgard (comics)|Asgard]] to enlist the aid of [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]], facing [[Surtur (Marvel Comics)|Surtur]] in the process.\n\nThe search for the five Nexus fragments again splits the heroes into teams. Captain America's group travels to the underwater city of Lemuria, but falls into a trap and must battle the Red King and several versions of the [[Hulk]] in Sakaar. Joined by the Hulk and [[Stingray (comics)|Stingray]], they return to Lemuria and defeat Attuma, retrieving a fragment. Moving on to [[Ancient Egypt]], they enter a [[Sphinx]] and join Horus of the [[Heliopolitans]] in facing [[Loki (comics)|Loki]] and [[N'Kantu, the Living Mummy]] to obtain another. Spider-Man's group visits the ''[[Marvel Noir]]'' version of Manhattan, where they help [[Iron Fist (comics)|Iron Fist]], [[Daredevil (Marvel Comics character)|Daredevil]], [[Luke Cage]], and [[Spider-Man Noir]] defeat the [[Kingpin (character)|Kingpin]]. Iron Fist accompanies them to K'un-L'un, where they fight [[Steel Serpent]] to free [[Shou-Lao]] and retrieve a Nexus fragment. Proceeding to the [[Alchemax]] building in ''[[Marvel 2099]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Nueva York, [[Spider-Gwen]] and [[Spider-Man 2099]] help them defeat the ''2099'' version of [[Green Goblin]] and a fusion of [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]] and [[Carnage (comics)|Carnage]] to obtain another fragment. In the [[Kree]] home world of Hala, the Guardians battle [[Ronan the Accuser]]. Meanwhile, in Attilan, the [[Inhumans]] defeat [[Maximus (comics)|Maximus]]. [[Black Bolt]] and [[Medusa (comics)|Medusa]] then head to Hala, where they free the Guardians from the control of the [[Supreme Intelligence]] and help them retrieve another fragment. As Kang observes the heroes' exploits and plots to destroy them, his assistant [[Ravonna]] becomes increasingly disturbed by his actions.\n\nWith the fragments gathered, the heroes assemble a device to bring Knowhere through a portal opened by Doctor Strange. Their first attempt nearly brings [[Ego the Living Planet]] through instead. Once Knowhere is in Chronopolis, they use an [[electromagnetic pulse]] to knock out the energy shield protecting Kang's citadel. As they begin their assault, Kang summons the ''Damocles''. Iron Man, Spider-Man, and [[Star-Lord]] disable the ship, battling [[Korvac]] and escaping before it crashes. Captain America, Captain Marvel, Doctor Strange, and Star-Lord enter the citadel and face Kang, who grows to gigantic size, uses the time crystal to reverse the ''Damocles''<nowiki>'</nowiki> destruction, and wields it as a sword. Captain America creates a giant solid hologram of himself and uses it to defeat Kang. Ravonna betrays Kang and uses the time crystal to turn him into a baby. The heroes celebrate their victory, and Ravonna promises to return the components of Chronopolis to their original places in time and space once the remaining villains are dealt with.\n\nIn a [[post-credits scene]], with everything restored to normal, Iron Man, Captain America, and Captain Marvel are visited by Ravonna in her new alias as Terminatrix. She is accompanied by an elderly Kang, the Supreme Intelligence, Cosmo, and Man-Thing, who inform the Avengers of a \"chronal fracture incident\".\n\n==Audio==\nDue to the game being affected by the [[2016\u201317 video game voice actor strike]], the cast from the previous game as well from ''[[Lego Marvel's Avengers]]'' did not return to reprise their roles as they were affiliated with the [[SAG-AFTRA|Screen Actors Guild\u2010American Federation of Television and Radio Artists (SAG-AFTRA)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nintendoeverything.com/lego-marvel-2-spotted-on-voice-actor-strike-document/ |title=\"LEGO Marvel 2\" spotted on voice actor strike document |author=Brian |date=3 November 2016 |website=Nintendo Everything}}</ref> While in favor of a new voice cast, [[Greg Miller (Internet celebrity)|Greg Miller]] voices [[Howard the Duck]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/agentm/status/888135929151447040 |title=#LEGOMarvel2 reveal: @GameOverGreggy voicing Howard the Duck who becomes the Iron Duck. Big role for Howard in the game. #MarvelGamesSDCC |first=Ryan |last=Penagos |date=20 July 2017 |website=twitter.com}}</ref> [[Peter Serafinowicz]] voices the game's antagonist Kang the Conqueror,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/arthur_parsons/status/905827593206865920 |title=Correct! |first=arthur |last=parsons |date=7 September 2017 |website=twitter.com}}</ref> [[Sacha Dhawan]] reprised his role as [[Steel Serpent]] from the ''[[Iron Fist (TV series)|Iron Fist]]'' [[Netflix]] television series<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/07/24/steel-serpent-explained-who-is-the-iron-fist-season-2-villain |title=Steel Serpent Explained: Who Is Davos, the Netflix Iron Fist Season 2 Villain? |first=Jesse |last=Schedeen |date=24 July 2018 |website=ign.com}}</ref> and Marvel Comics writer [[Stan Lee]] returned to voice himself.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/video-games/Lego-Marvel-Superheroes-2/Stan-Lee/ |title=Stan Lee |author= |date= |website=Behind The Voice Actors}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (XONE) 76/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref><br>(NS) 75/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for Switch Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref><br>(PS4) 73/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/lego-marvel-super-heroes-2 |title=Lego Marvel Super Heroes 2 for PlayStation 4 Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>\n}}\nThe game was well received by critics, who praised the game's linguistic content as well as the possibility to play with various Marvel characters.\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Result !! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Game Critics Awards]]\n| Best Family/Social Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/nominees.html |title=Game Critics Awards: Best of E3 2017 (2017 Nominees) |website=[[Game Critics Awards]] |accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Gamescom|Gamescom 2017]]\n| Best Family Game\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cgmagonline.com/2017/08/21/gamescom-2017-award-nominees/ |title=Gamescom 2017 Award Nominees |first=Zubi |last=Khan |date=21 August 2017 |website=CGM |accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\" | New York Game Awards 2018\n| Central Park Children's Zoo Aw